<HEAD>Dollar And Stocks Both Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar finished higher Wednesday in trading
against the Japanese yen in Tokyo, while stock prices posted a
strong gain.
   The dollar closed at 125.35 yen, up 0.55 yen from Tuesday's
finish. It opened the day at 125.23 yen and ranged between 125.10
and 125.37 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, a 193.60-point winner Tuesday, added another
287.21 points, or 1.04 percent, to close the day's trading at
27,703.91.
   ``The thrust of the dollar's upward momentum is not so strong,''
said a senior dealer at a major commercial bank who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
   ``Share prices rallied almost across the board, helped by the
notion among many market participants that rising U.S. interest
rates have peaked out,'' said Seiichiro Kita of Daiwa Securities, a
major Japanese brokerage.
   Kita and other securities company officials said the Tokyo stock
market was also encouraged by a 74.68-point surge in the Dow Jones
industrial average on Wall Street overnight.
</TEXT>
