<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF-GreaseDeath     06-01 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Grease Death,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Would-Be Burglar Found Dead In Restaurant Vent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A would-be burglar who tried to enter a
restaurant through an exhaust vent got stuck and was found dead
with his feet in a vat of hot fat, police said.
   ``He got wedged in there and his feet dropped down into that hot
grease. He couldn't get up and he couldn't get down,'' police Lt.
Carl Goolsby said Tuesday.
   Dr. O.C. Smith, a Shelby County medical examiner, said Dennis
Johnson, 34, was apparently asphyxiated.
   ``By being wedged in the vent it compressed his chest and he
couldn't breathe,'' Smith said.
   Johnson suffered third-degree burns over his feet and ankles,
but those were not sufficient to kill him, Smith said.
   Goolsby said Johnson apparently planned to burglarize the fried
chicken restaurant by crawling through the rooftop vent after the
business closed early Tuesday.
</TEXT>
