<HEAD>Cuba Says It Seized American Yacht Crammed With Marijuana</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Cuban coast guard has seized an American
yacht with three men on board found carrying about 13,200 pounds of
marijuana, the Cuban news agency Prensa Latina reported.
   In a dispatch from Havana on Tuesday, the agency quoted unnamed
Interior Ministry sources saying the yacht Caribbean King was
intercepted and seized Monday afternoon off the town of Mor, in
Holguin Province.
   It identified the three men only as a Cuban living in Miami and
two citizens of the Dominican Republic, and did not give their
names.
   The drug, contained in 208 packages, was inicinerated by Cuban
authorities, said the dispatch, monitored in Mexico City.
