<HEAD>Guests Evacuated From A Luxury Hotel During Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEL AVIV, Israel (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire broke out in the basement of a
luxury hotel and forced the evacutation of 400 guests, including
Spanish guitarist Paco De Lucia. Officials said two hotel employees
were injured.
   A maintenance manager and a worker at the Dan Panorama Hotel
suffered minor burns, and a firefighter suffered smoke inhalation,
hotel officials said.
   But no guests were injured and there was no substantial damage,
