<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Turkey-Shooting     06-01 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Turkey-Shooting,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gunman Kills Three, Then Commits Suicide In Ankara Hotel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man shot and killed three people today,
including the chairman of the Istanbul Chamber of Commerce, at a
restaurant in a downtown hotel, the Anatolia News Agency reported.
   The assailant then shot himself in the head and was killed
instantly, the report from the semi-official news agency said.
   Anatolia identified the victims as Niyazi Adiguzel, chairman of
the Istanbul Chamber of Commerce, Mevlut Isik, a journalist from
the daily newspaper Turkiye, and Davut Celik.
   The assailant, identified as Kursad Ozkan, and Adiguzel argued
before Ozkan drew a gun and started firing, first at Adiguzel and
then at other diners in the restaurant of the Grand Ankara Hotel,
the agency said.
   It said Isik was sitting at a table next to Adiguzel's.
   Police could not be reached immediately for details on the
shooting.
</TEXT>
