<HEAD>___</HEAD>
<HEAD>US-SOVIET TIES</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Reagan said his personal relationship with Gorbachev ``continued
to deepen and improve'' and their fundamental differences
``continue to recede.'' Nonetheless, he said, ``I am never going to
relax my belief in the need for verification of agreements that we
might make.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>___</HEAD>
<HEAD>EVIL EMPIRE</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   The president said his disavowal of an earlier reference to the
Soviet Union as an ``evil empire'' resulted from changes instituted
by Gorbachev. He said he'd read Gorbachev's book, ``Perestroika,''
about economic reforms and ``I found much in it that I agree with.''
