<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Obit-Friebus     06-01 0106</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Friebus,0110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>TV Actress Who Played `Dobie Gillis' Mom Dead At 79</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGUNA NIGUEL, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Florida Friebus, who played the
title character's mother on the 1950s series ``The Many Loves of
Dobie Gillis'' and a group therapy patient on ``The Bob Newhart
Show,'' has died. She was 79.
   Miss Friebus, who died Friday, was a veteran of numerous stage
productions on the East Coast before coming to Los Angeles in 1955.
   She portrayed the dimwitted, sweater-knitting Mrs. Bakerman on
``The Bob Newhart Show'' during its 1972-78 run.
   Miss Friebus had no survivors. In accordance with her wishes no
memorial service will be held.
</TEXT>
