<HEAD>Rob West German Tour Bus at Rest Stop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NIMES, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two armed men held up a bus carrying West
German tourists early Wednesday and made off with money, jewelry
and suitcases, police said.
   None of the 40 passengers was injured in the robbery at about 3
a.m. at a rest step along the A-9 highway between Nimes and Avignon
in southern France.
   Police said two armed men, their faces hidden with hoods,
boarded the bus and forced passengers to hand over their valuables.
They took off in a waiting car driven by an accomplice.
   The bus was coming from Spain and headed to several towns in
West Germany. It continued its trip several hours after the
robbery. Police said the passengers were frightened but unharmed.
</TEXT>
