<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--NATO-Commander     06-01 0134</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--NATO-Commander,0138</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Alliance Appoints New Atlantic Commander</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NATO said Wednesday it appointed U.S.
Adm. Frank B. Kelso II as Supreme Allied Commander Atlantic to
replace U.S. Adm. Lee Baggett Jr.
   Baggett is retiring from the Navy, the U.S. mission to NATO said.
   A statement by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization said its
Defense Planning Committee, meeting at alliance headquarters,
``agreed with great regret to release'' Baggett from his post at
President Reagan's request.
   The NATO panel said it also accepted Reagan's request that Kelso
be named as Baggett's replacement. The transfer of commands is to
take place this fall, NATO said.
   Kelso is commander-in-chief of the U.S. Atlantic Fleet and
deputy commander in chief of the U.S. Atlantic Command. Baggett was
appointed to his NATO position in September 1985.
</TEXT>
