<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--SchoolSalaries     06-01 0114</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--School Salaries,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Average Public School Salaries Reported in Survey</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An education research group says its survey of
1,000 public school district found average salaries this year
ranged from $28,230 for teachers to $68,147 for superintendents.
   Principals averaged $43,664 at the elementary school level,
$47,078 in middle schools and $50,512 in high schools, the
Educational Research Service said.
   Assistant principals received an average of $36,364 in
elementary schools, $40,093 in middle schools and $41,839 in high
schools.
   Assistant superintendents averaged $56,894, while subject-area
supervisors earned $41,086, said the research group, which has
conducted annual salary surveys since 1973.
   The salary data was reported in the May issue of Principal
magazine.
</TEXT>
