<1ST_LINE>r p AM-BRF--Convention-Mississippi     06-01 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Convention-Mississippi,160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mississippi Hoping To Cash In On Republican Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BILOXI, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mississippi Gulf Coast officials say they
hope a good share of Republican National Convention delegates
traveling to New Orleans will also drop in on the bordering
Magnolia state.
   Republicans crowding New Orleans for the Aug. 15-18 convention
will receive delegate packets that promote Mississippi attractions
along with those in the host city.
   ``We have always wanted to include the Gulf Coast, especially
since it is only an hour away,'' said Peggy Wilson, chairwoman of
the convention's media and hospitality committee. ``I have gone to
Mississippi to let the Mississippi people feel this is their
convention.''
   Since Vice President George Bush has locked up the GOP
presidential nomination, delegates will have more free time to
visit Mississippi attractions, said Sen. Bob Usey of Gulfport,
Bush's coast campaign coordinator.
   ``New Orleans can only offer so much. I think we will be
pleasantly surprised,'' he added.
</TEXT>
