<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Brites     06-01 0362</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Brites,0375</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bright and Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GILROY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six months of top-secret research may be
worth all the suspense involved if the two McDonald's restaurants
here are permitted to offer an innovation on their menu: ``Gilroy
garlic'' on hamburgers.
   ``We're the garlic capital of the world and we want to continue
that fame in a fast-food restaurant,'' said David Kaplan, owner of
one of the McDonald's and the man who came up with the idea for the
garlic spread.
   Not too surprisingly, grower Don Christopher, who would supply
the garlic, said: ``Garlic's the in-thing to eat.''
   At McDonald's San Jose office, regional Vice President Tom Doran
said the company favors Kaplan's idea but has to see the packaging
and contents before it grants final approval. Prototypes of the
spread were flown to the office Wednesday.
   Actually, more garlic is grown around Fresno than Gilroy. Only
420 acres of garlic are planted in and around Gilroy, while Fresno
has 12,700 acres, agricultural officials said.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NORFOLK, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For the first time in Navy history, the
annual shore-based Sailor of the Year is a woman, and Petty Officer
1st Class Beth L. Blevins said Wednesday she was ``shellshocked.''
   ``I'm very sure I was not chosen because I was a female sailor.
I was chosen because I was a good sailor,'' she said.
   As part of the honor, she will receive a promotion to chief
petty officer, be reassigned to the Pentagon, received the Navy
Commendation Medal and get a week's worth of rest and relaxation at
any location in the United States.
   Blevins is the leading petty officer of the airframes division
at Fleet Logistics Support Squadron 40 at the Norfolk Naval Air
Station.
   ``It has been a real long, hard road for a lot of females who
are in non-traditional ratings,'' she said. ``We are just starting
to earn the respect and the recognition for the job we do. It is a
very good opportunity to show everyone in the Navy how far we have
come and much good we do for the military.''
   Similar awards are given to sea-based sailors of the Atlantic,
Pacific, and Reserve Force fleets.
</TEXT>
