<HEAD>Campbell Makes Offer For British Frozen Food Firm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Campbell Soup Co. says it will make a $200
million tender offer to purchase the remaining shares of Freshbake
Foods Group PLC, in a move to gain strength in the European frozen
food market.
   Campbell already owns or has commitments for about 51 percent of
Freshbake's stock.
   The company said Tuesday it will offer 162 pence, or about $3,
for each of more than 67 million outstanding shares of Freshbake, a
public company based in Orpington, Kent, England.
   Camden-based Campbell will pay for the shares in cash, the
equivalent of interest-bearing notes, or any combination of both at
the option of the shareholder.
   Freshbake is believed to be the third largest frozen food
producer in the United Kingdom with annual sales of more than $300
million. It manufactures pastries and meats, and markets frozen
vegetables for private label sales.
   ``We see important benefits from combining Freshbake's growing
business, its experience and its successful management with
Campbell's global frozen food technology and brand strength,'' said
John W. Argabright, president of Campbell International.
