surprise at the market's sudden show of strength on Tuesday.
   Unexpected as it was, the rally raised hopes that stocks had
pulled out of the slump that had experienced for several weeks.
   The government's report that the index of leading economic
indicators rose 0.2 percent in April was in line with expectations,
and brokers said it had little discernible effect on the market.
