<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Armtek-Pirelli     06-01 0222</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Armtek-Pirelli,0233</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Armtek Finalizes Sale Of Armstrong Unit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Armtek Corp. has completed the sale of
its Armstrong Tire Co. and other assets to the Pirelli Group of
Italy for $197 million, said Armtek chairman Frank R. O'Keefe Jr.
   The sale gives the company the ability to focus on its other
businesses, O'Keefe said. They are Blackstone, a manufacturer of
heat exchange components; Copolymer Rubber and Chemical Corp., and
Dayco Products Inc., a maker of automotive belts and hoses.
   Pirelli plans to make a three-year investment of $100 million in
improving overall quality and creating new production capacity for
Pirelli passenger car tires in the United States, Daniel Cutrone,
director of marketing for Armstrong, said Tuesday.
   Capital expenditures are also planned for Armstrong products.
   The sale includes Armstrong Tire production facilities in Des
Moines, Iowa; Nashville, Tenn., and Hanford, Calif.; the Extruded
Products business in Little Rock, Ark., and the headquarters
building in New Haven..
   Armtek headquarters staff will remain in the New Haven building
at least temporarily, Cutrone said.
   Pirelli sought last year to acquire 80 percent of Armstrong
Tire, but the talks ended after the two companies could not agree
on the value of the proposed buyout.
   Pirelli recently lost out to Japan's Bridgestone Corp. in a bid
to purchase Firestone Tire & Rubber Co.
</TEXT>
