<2ND_LINE>AM-OPEC Delay,0079</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>OPEC Meeting Postponed, Report Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries
has postponed its ministerial conference in Vienna next week to
avoid clashing with an Arab leaders' meeting in Algiers, the
Financial Times reported in Thursday editions.
   The business daily quoted unidentified sources as saying that
because of the Arab summit, the OPEC meeting scheduled to begin on
Wednesday will be postponed to either June 10 or June 11.
